@vorburger Most of those dependencies (gson, quartz etc) are indeed part of spring-boot-dependencies BOM. 

But I've just noticed we are importing into dependency management spring-framework-bom - which contains just the Spring framework and doesn't contain any of these dependencies.  

So if we switch dependency management to import spring-boot-dependencies instead, we should be able to get rid of many of these versions. In fact, shouldn't we be able to avoid mentioning them altogether in build.gradle given that the imported POM already references them?
